01:29.480 --> 01:31.700
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:31.830 --> 01:33.571
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:33.702 --> 01:35.573
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.704 --> 01:37.488
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.619 --> 01:40.187
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.317 --> 01:43.712
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.842 --> 01:46.584
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.817 --> 02:03.732
-[SOFT MUSIC]

02:09.433 --> 02:10.565
-LOGAN: CAROLINE!

02:13.872 --> 02:14.960
-LOGAN!

02:18.486 --> 02:19.878
HI.
-HEY.

02:20.488 --> 02:21.706
READY FOR YOUR LESSON?

02:21.837 --> 02:23.578
-[LAUGHS] WHAT LESSON?

02:23.708 --> 02:26.233
-I THOUGHT YOU WANTED TO LEARN
HOW TO RIDE A WAVE RUNNER.

02:26.363 --> 02:27.973
-WELL, YEAH, I DO.

02:28.104 --> 02:30.150
-WELL, NOW'S YOUR BIG CHANCE.

02:31.063 --> 02:32.630
-ALL RIGHT. WHY NOT?

02:35.894 --> 02:38.419
THIS IS SO MUCH FUN!

02:40.464 --> 02:41.813
-LOGAN: HANG ON!

02:41.944 --> 02:44.207
-WHOO!
-WHOO!

03:16.761 --> 03:18.720
-GOD, YOU GOTTA ADMIT,
HE'S GOOD.

03:19.503 --> 03:21.549
-WHAT, JUST BECAUSE HE'S GOT
A COUPLE OF HOT SHOT MOVES?

03:21.679 --> 03:23.681
-NO, BECAUSE HE STOLE
STEPHANIE'S SISTER

03:23.812 --> 03:25.770
RIGHT OUT FROM
UNDERNEATH YOUR NOSE.

03:26.728 --> 03:27.990
-THANKS, NEWMIE.

03:30.601 --> 03:32.908
-OKAY, YOU OKAY?

03:33.909 --> 03:36.128
-OKAY.
-NOTHING FANCY NOW.
TAKE IT NICE AND SLOW.

03:36.259 --> 03:38.218
-OKAY, OKAY.
-THERE'S A LOT OF POWER
UNDER THIS LITTLE BOY.

03:38.348 --> 03:39.958
-ALL RIGHT, COME ON NOW.
-OKAY.

03:41.395 --> 03:42.570
[LAUGHS]

03:42.700 --> 03:43.919
-OKAY.
-LOGAN: OKAY.

03:44.049 --> 03:44.876
-ALL RIGHT, WHAT DO I DO?

03:46.661 --> 03:48.402
-WHOA!

03:48.532 --> 03:49.664
-WAIT A MINUTE!
-CAROLINE: WHAT IS IT?

03:49.794 --> 03:52.014
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:52.144 --> 03:53.711
-SOMEBODY'S WAIST
UP. SWITCH BACK.

03:53.842 --> 03:55.278
COME ON, COME ON!
-CAROLINE: WHAT? OKAY!

03:57.237 --> 03:59.195
-YOU READY? HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

03:59.326 --> 04:02.285
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

04:24.089 --> 04:25.526
-[SCREAMS]

04:26.657 --> 04:29.443
-SHE'S IN TROUBLE. LET'S GO.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.552
I GOT YOU. IT'S OKAY.

04:57.122 --> 04:59.560
-DO ME A FAVOR. CALL TOWER
12 AND MAKE SURE EVERYBODY

04:59.690 --> 05:01.170
STAYS OUT OF THE
WATER THERE, OKAY?

05:01.301 --> 05:02.171
-OKAY.

05:03.215 --> 05:04.956
-HOBIE.
-HOBIE: DAD!

05:05.087 --> 05:06.044
-COME HERE, MAN.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.309
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
BACK HERE SO SOON?

05:09.439 --> 05:10.266
-I MISSED YA.

05:10.397 --> 05:11.789
-I MISSED YOU, TOO, MAN.

05:13.051 --> 05:15.619
-YOU WERE RIGHT, DAD. YOU
SAID I'D GET OVER MY FEAR.

05:15.750 --> 05:17.882
I DID, AT LEAST I HOPE I DID.

05:18.013 --> 05:20.407
GUESS I WON'T KNOW FOR SURE
UNTIL MY FIRST AFTER SHOCK.

05:20.537 --> 05:22.322
HAS THERE BEEN ANY?

05:22.452 --> 05:24.976
-YEAH, YEAH, A COUPLE LITTLE
ONES. NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

05:26.238 --> 05:27.109
-HI.

05:28.632 --> 05:29.981
-HI.

05:30.112 --> 05:31.156
-HOBIE TALKED
ABOUT YOU SO MUCH,

05:31.287 --> 05:32.767
I STARTED MISSING YOU MYSELF.

05:32.897 --> 05:34.029
YOU LOOK GREAT.

05:37.598 --> 05:38.468
-YOU LOOK GOOD, TOO.

05:38.599 --> 05:39.469
-THANKS.

05:40.035 --> 05:41.776
-WELL, SO WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS?

05:41.906 --> 05:43.386
I MEAN, CAN YOU STAY AWHILE OR
YOU GOTTA RUSH RIGHT BACK?

05:43.517 --> 05:45.388
-WELL, AFTER THE
WINTER WE'VE HAD,

05:45.519 --> 05:47.216
I WAS REALLY LOOKING
FORWARD TO SPENDING

05:47.347 --> 05:48.783
A FEW DAYS ON THE BEACH.

05:48.913 --> 05:50.611
-YOU CAME TO THE RIGHT PLACE.

05:50.741 --> 05:53.353
-HEY, TELL YOU WHAT. I'M
GONNA GO GET OUR STUFF.

05:53.483 --> 05:56.834
YOU GUYS JUST TALK
AMONGST YOURSELVES.

05:58.793 --> 06:00.925
-I WAS AFRAID I'D
NEVER SEE HIM AGAIN.

06:01.056 --> 06:03.145
-OH, LISTEN, A
COUPLE WEEKS IN OHIO

06:03.275 --> 06:05.582
MAKES YOU REALIZE THAT NO
MATTER HOW MUCH SHAKING

06:05.713 --> 06:07.236
GOES ON AROUND HERE,
THIS IS STILL A PRETTY

06:07.367 --> 06:08.585
GREAT PLACE TO LIVE.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.108
-YEAH.

06:10.239 --> 06:11.240
-YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN
TOYING WITH THE IDEA

06:11.371 --> 06:13.111
OF MOVING BACK HERE MYSELF.

06:13.242 --> 06:14.374
-YOU HAVE?

06:14.504 --> 06:15.897
-YEAH.

06:16.027 --> 06:18.987
YEAH, EVER SINCE KEN AND I
BROKE UP, I DON'T KNOW,

06:19.117 --> 06:20.858
IT'S JUST BEEN LONELY.

06:20.989 --> 06:23.295
-YEAH, WHAT HAPPENED THERE?
I NEVER GOT THE WHOLE STORY.

06:23.948 --> 06:25.950
-I DON'T KNOW, AFTER THE
PLANE CRASH, IT'S JUST--

06:26.081 --> 06:27.865
EVERYTHING CHANGED.

06:27.996 --> 06:29.954
YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE HE COULDN'T
LOOK ME IN THE EYE ANY MORE.

06:30.694 --> 06:32.130
HE INSISTED THAT
HE STILL LOVED ME,

06:32.261 --> 06:33.958
BUT WE BOTH KNEW
THE MAGIC WAS GONE.

06:34.089 --> 06:36.221
-I'M SORRY, GAYLE,
REALLY, I AM.

06:36.352 --> 06:37.832
-IT JUST WASN'T MEANT TO BE.

06:38.833 --> 06:40.791
ANYWAY, I'M OUT THERE
AGAIN LOOKING FOR LOVE

06:40.922 --> 06:41.705
IN ALL THE WRONG PLACES.

06:41.836 --> 06:42.967
-[CHUCKLES]

06:44.360 --> 06:45.579
-WELL, YOU SEEM PRETTY HAPPY.

06:45.709 --> 06:47.711
-YEAH, WELL, THAT'S
BECAUSE OF OUR SON.

06:49.365 --> 06:52.063
YOU KNOW, I'D FORGOTTEN WHAT
IT FELT LIKE TO BE A MOTHER.

06:53.021 --> 06:55.110
IT'S NOT GOING TO BE EASY
FOR ME TO LET HIM GO AGAIN.

06:56.154 --> 06:59.941
-[SOFT MUSIC]

07:07.427 --> 07:08.776
-YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

07:09.472 --> 07:12.606
-YEAH. WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU DOING OUT THERE?

07:12.736 --> 07:15.435
-MATT, WHY ARE YOU MAKING
SUCH A BIG DEAL ABOUT THIS?

07:15.565 --> 07:18.350
-BECAUSE YOU CAME WITHIN
A FOOT FROM BEING CRUSHED
BY A WAVE RUNNER.

07:18.481 --> 07:20.657
-A BLOKE WAS DOWN IN THE
WATER. HE NEEDED HELP.

07:21.266 --> 07:23.921
-YOU DON'T JEOPARDIZE
ONE LIFE TO SAVE ANOTHER.

07:25.140 --> 07:26.402
YOU'RE A LIFEGUARD,
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT.

07:27.272 --> 07:28.622
-OKAY, LET'S CUT THE BULL.

07:29.492 --> 07:31.799
WE BOTH KNOW THIS ISN'T
ABOUT BEING LIFEGUARDS.

07:31.929 --> 07:32.930
IT'S ABOUT HER.

07:34.671 --> 07:37.326
YOU CAN'T STAND THE FACT THAT
CAROLINE WANTS TO BE WITH ME.

07:38.762 --> 07:40.285
IT'S EATING YOU UP.

07:41.417 --> 07:42.418
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:42.549 --> 07:44.246
-MATT, DON'T BE STUPID.

07:45.290 --> 07:46.422
MATT! LOGAN!

07:46.553 --> 07:51.035
STOP IT, YOU GUYS.
SOMEBODY GET SOME HELP!

07:52.515 --> 07:54.038
PLEASE.
-ALL RIGHT, KNOCK IT OFF.

07:54.952 --> 07:56.084
-COME ON!

07:56.214 --> 07:57.346
-WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

07:57.477 --> 07:58.956
-DON'T LOOK AT ME!

07:59.087 --> 08:01.045
-MATT, I WANT YOUR
INCIDENT REPORT ON MY DESK

08:01.176 --> 08:02.046
BEFORE THE END OF THE DAY.

08:04.222 --> 08:05.441
-THIS ISN'T FINISHED!

08:07.443 --> 08:08.357
-CAROLINE?

08:09.489 --> 08:10.272
-YEAH?

08:10.402 --> 08:11.839
-I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.

08:16.321 --> 08:18.933
-MITCH, MAYBE YOU SHOULD HAVE
A TALK WITH MATT AND LOGAN.

08:19.063 --> 08:21.718
-AH, I DON'T KNOW.
I GOT A BETTER IDEA.

08:21.849 --> 08:24.242
-YEAH, SHIP LOGAN WITH
HIS BUTT BACK TO TASMANIA.

08:24.373 --> 08:27.115
-NO. ASSIGN THEM DORY DUTY.

08:28.029 --> 08:29.726
[CHUCKLES]

08:29.857 --> 08:32.467
-DORY DUTY. THAT
IS A GOOD IDEA.

08:32.599 --> 08:37.038
-I COME UP WITH ONE EVERY
YEAR AND WE KNOW HOW IT GOES.

08:40.041 --> 08:42.390
-[SOOTHING MUSIC]

08:47.701 --> 08:48.919
-[LAUGHS]

08:49.050 --> 08:51.139
-[TALKING OVER ONE ANOTHER]

08:51.269 --> 08:52.793
-GAYLE: NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

08:52.923 --> 08:54.316
THIS WAS A VERY BAD LOOK
FOR YOU. TRUST ME ON THAT.

08:54.446 --> 08:56.231
-MITCH: OH, REMEMBER THAT DAY?

08:56.361 --> 08:58.059
-GAYLE: HOBIE, LOOK
AT YOUR FATHER. CAN YOU

08:58.189 --> 08:59.843
BELIEVE THIS?
-HOBIE: MY GOSH.

08:59.974 --> 09:01.323
-NOT THAT I-- I MEAN,
LOOK AT, OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE.

09:01.453 --> 09:02.803
-WHAT'S UP WITH THAT
SKY BLUE SUIT, DAD?

09:02.933 --> 09:04.369
THAT'S PRETTY FUNNY.

09:04.500 --> 09:06.110
-I LOVE THAT SUIT. I
STILL HAVE THAT SUIT.

09:06.241 --> 09:07.459
IT'S IN MY CLOSEST.
-GAYLE: PEOPLE THOUGHT
THAT WAS COOL.

09:07.590 --> 09:09.113
-HOBESTER!

09:09.244 --> 09:11.159
-HOBIE: OH, MY GOSH.
-GAYLE: YOU WERE SO CUTE.

09:12.160 --> 09:13.030
-MITCH: OH, LOOK AT THAT.

09:13.640 --> 09:16.251
-YOU WERE SO CUTE.
YOU WERE SO CUTE.

09:16.947 --> 09:17.774
-THAT'S IT.

09:21.648 --> 09:23.388
BRINGS BACK A LOT
OF MEMORIES, HUH?

09:23.519 --> 09:25.913
-YEAH, YOU KNOW IT KIND
OF MAKES YOU WONDER WHY

09:26.043 --> 09:26.914
WE EVER SPLIT UP.

09:29.046 --> 09:31.005
-OH, BOY, I DON'T
KNOW ABOUT YOU GUYS,

09:31.135 --> 09:32.963
BUT I AM EXHAUSTED.

09:33.094 --> 09:35.444
-WELL, YOU'RE STILL ON
EASTERN TIME.
IT'S LIKE ALMOST 3:00

09:35.575 --> 09:36.401
IN THE MORNING.

09:36.532 --> 09:37.533
-OH, YEAH.

09:40.449 --> 09:42.103
-BETTER CALL IT A NIGHT, PAL.

09:42.233 --> 09:43.757
-YEAH, I THINK SO.

09:43.887 --> 09:45.149
-DO YOU WANT ME TO
COME UP WITH YOU?

09:45.802 --> 09:48.022
-MOM, I'M 13 YEARS
OLD. GIVE ME A BREAK.

09:48.152 --> 09:49.371
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

09:49.501 --> 09:51.068
-EXCUSE ME, I'M
STILL GONNA COME UP

09:51.199 --> 09:52.243
AND KISS YOU GOOD NIGHT
BEFORE I GO BACK TO THE HOTEL.

09:52.374 --> 09:53.984
-FINE. NIGHT, MOM, NIGHT, DAD.

09:54.115 --> 09:55.029
-GOOD NIGHT, PAL.
-GAYLE: NIGHT, HONEY.

09:59.729 --> 10:01.339
SEEMS LIKE OLD
TIMES, DOESN'T IT?

10:02.166 --> 10:03.951
-YEAH. IT DOES.

10:04.778 --> 10:06.431
-YOU REMEMBER WHEN WE
MOVED INTO THIS HOUSE?

10:06.562 --> 10:08.390
-[LAUGHS] YEAH.

10:08.520 --> 10:11.045
-THE FIRST NIGHT, WE STILL
DIDN'T HAVE ANY FURNITURE.

10:11.175 --> 10:12.568
-UNBELIEVABLE.

10:12.699 --> 10:13.700
-AND REMEMBER, YOU
LIT A FIRE AND WE ENDED

10:13.830 --> 10:14.918
UP SLEEPING ON THE FLOOR?

10:15.049 --> 10:16.050
-THAT WAS NICE.
-GAYLE: YEAH.

10:16.180 --> 10:17.051
-THAT WAS NICE.

10:18.400 --> 10:20.184
-IT'S NICE THAT WE
CAN BE CLOSE AGAIN.

10:20.315 --> 10:22.926
-YEAH. YEAH, IT IS.

10:25.450 --> 10:28.584
-MITCH, BEFORE WHEN YOU ASKED
ME WHY I DIDN'T MARRY KEN,

10:28.715 --> 10:31.674
I WASN'T COMPLETELY
HONEST WITH YOU.

10:33.154 --> 10:34.677
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:34.808 --> 10:37.332
-THE REAL REASON WHY I COULDN'T
GO THROUGH WITH IT WAS...

10:38.638 --> 10:40.509
I REALIZED I WAS STILL
IN LOVE WITH YOU.

10:40.640 --> 10:43.294
-[SOFT MUSIC]

10:43.425 --> 10:44.905
AND I KNOW YOU'RE PROBABLY
GONNA THINK I'M CRAZY

10:45.035 --> 10:46.776
BUT DOESN'T THIS FEEL RIGHT?

10:52.173 --> 10:56.743
LOOK, I FEEL LIKE WE'VE BEEN
CHEATING HOBIE AND OURSELVES

10:56.873 --> 10:58.527
OUT OF HAVING A REAL FAMILY.

11:02.270 --> 11:04.968
I MEAN, I THINK WE BOTH
KNOW IT DOESN'T GET

11:05.099 --> 11:06.404
ANY BETTER THAN THIS.

11:09.016 --> 11:10.408
I WANNA COME HOME.

11:14.282 --> 11:15.675
WILL YOU TAKE ME BACK?

11:19.200 --> 11:21.855
-DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG I'VE
WAITED FOR YOU TO SAY THAT?

11:29.732 --> 11:32.517
-[SOFT MUSIC]

11:39.742 --> 11:40.917
-HEY, DAD, HAVE
YOU SEEN MY RADIO?

11:41.048 --> 11:42.266
I WANNA CATCH THE SURF REPORT.

11:44.268 --> 11:45.139
MOM.

11:45.269 --> 11:46.706
-GOOD MORNING.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.317
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:49.447 --> 11:51.362
-I AM FIXING YOU BREAKFAST.

11:51.493 --> 11:53.538
YOU GOTTA EAT SOMETHING
BEFORE YOU HIT THE BEACH.

11:53.669 --> 11:55.105
-YOU MEAN YOU WERE
HERE ALL NIGHT?

11:55.236 --> 11:56.498
-YES, I WAS.

11:56.628 --> 11:57.629
-ON THE COUCH?

11:59.109 --> 12:00.807
-ON THE FLOOR ACTUALLY.

12:03.418 --> 12:04.724
-MORNING, HOBSTER.

12:10.164 --> 12:11.034
DID YOU TELL HIM?

12:12.122 --> 12:12.949
-TELL ME WHAT?

12:15.604 --> 12:17.693
-YOUR FATHER AND I ARE
GETTING MARRIED AGAIN.

12:19.216 --> 12:20.217
-FOR REAL?

12:20.348 --> 12:21.828
-[CHUCKLES]

12:21.958 --> 12:23.960
-YOU GUYS ARE SERIOUS?
THIS ISN'T A DREAM?

12:24.091 --> 12:26.441
-YOU THINK YOU CAN
HANDLE ME BEING AROUND?

12:26.571 --> 12:29.183
-OF COURSE, I CAN. I LOVE YOU!

12:30.445 --> 12:32.447
-[LAUGHS] I LOVE YOU, TOO.

12:34.754 --> 12:35.929
WAY TO GO, DAD!

12:36.059 --> 12:36.886
-YEAH!

12:38.279 --> 12:42.544
-[CHEERFUL MUSIC]

13:08.135 --> 13:12.574
♪ INFINITELY

13:12.704 --> 13:17.666
♪ I'M ON YOUR SIDE

13:17.797 --> 13:22.758
♪ I'LL KEEP YOU WITH ME

13:22.889 --> 13:25.543
♪ 'CAUSE YOU ARE

13:25.674 --> 13:30.287
♪ YOU ARE MINE

13:38.948 --> 13:42.822
♪ I KNEW SOMEDAY WE'D
♪ FIND OUR WAY BACK HERE

13:44.432 --> 13:47.827
♪ TOGETHER AGAIN NOW
♪ THE SKIES HAVE CLEARED

13:49.698 --> 13:53.049
♪ I'VE GOT ALL THIS LOVE TO GIVE TO YOU

13:54.529 --> 13:58.446
♪ 'CAUSE YOU'RE THE FAMILY
♪ THAT I GET TO CHOOSE

13:59.447 --> 14:02.319
♪ I WON'T LET GO THIS TIME

14:04.408 --> 14:07.977
♪ SO TAKE YOUR HAND IN MINE

14:09.544 --> 14:13.940
♪ INFINITELY

14:14.070 --> 14:19.075
♪ I'M ON YOUR SIDE

14:19.206 --> 14:24.167
♪ I'LL KEEP YOU WITH ME

14:24.298 --> 14:27.388
♪ 'CAUSE YOU ARE

14:27.518 --> 14:30.739
♪ YOU ARE MINE

14:52.021 --> 14:53.849
-I'M NOT QUITE
SURE I GET THE POINT

14:53.980 --> 14:55.546
OF THIS EXERCISE, LIEUTENANT.

14:56.460 --> 14:59.986
-IT'S NOT AN EXERCISE. IT'S
CRUEL AND UNUSUAL PUNISHMENT.

15:00.116 --> 15:02.379
-THE POINT IS TEACH
YOU TWO, MACHO MANIACS,

15:02.510 --> 15:04.251
THAT YOU'RE PLAYING
FOR THE SAME TEAM.

15:04.381 --> 15:06.296
THE DORY IS A PERFECT
METAPHOR FOR TEAMWORK

15:06.427 --> 15:07.732
'CAUSE IT REQUIRES
TWO INDIVIDUALS

15:07.863 --> 15:09.256
TO FUNCTION AS A SINGLE UNIT.

15:09.952 --> 15:11.954
YOU DON'T ROW TOGETHER,
YOU'LL NEVER MAKE IT BACK.

15:12.955 --> 15:16.132
OKAY, YOU GOT WATER,
EMERGENCY GEAR, RADIO

15:16.263 --> 15:17.699
AND EACH OTHER.

15:17.829 --> 15:19.092
-[GRUNTS]

15:19.788 --> 15:21.181
-WELL, WE COULDN'T
ASK FOR ANYTHING MORE.

15:21.311 --> 15:22.660
-[ENGINE REVVING]
-ALL RIGHT, GOOD LUCK,

15:22.791 --> 15:23.879
GENTLEMEN, I HOPE
WHEN I SEE YOU NEXT,

15:24.010 --> 15:25.141
YOU'LL HAVE WORKED THINGS OUT.

15:33.976 --> 15:36.457
-OH, CHEER UP, MATE. IT'S
NOT THE END OF THE WORLD.

15:36.587 --> 15:39.112
WHO KNOWS, BY THE
TIME WE REACH SHORE,

15:39.242 --> 15:40.591
WE MIGHT BE THE BEST OF FRIENDS.

15:41.244 --> 15:42.724
STRANGER THINGS HAVE HAPPENED.

15:43.333 --> 15:44.247
-NOT IN YOUR LIFETIME.

15:44.378 --> 15:45.857
-[LAUGHS]

15:50.210 --> 15:51.646
-OH, DID YOU DISCOVER
THAT YOU'RE IN LOVE

15:51.776 --> 15:53.256
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS?

15:53.387 --> 15:54.997
THAT'S SO ROMANTIC.

15:55.128 --> 15:57.826
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO
SAY, I'M TOO STUNNED.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.175
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

15:59.306 --> 16:00.220
-MITCH AND GAYLE
ARE GETTING MARRIED.

16:01.308 --> 16:02.526
-MARRIED AGAIN?

16:03.571 --> 16:06.400
-YEAH, YEAH. IT'S PRETTY
HARD TO BELIEVE, HUH?

16:06.530 --> 16:07.967
-AH, NO, NO. IT'S GREAT.

16:08.619 --> 16:09.490
CONGRATULATIONS.

16:09.620 --> 16:10.926
-MITCH: MMM, THANKS.

16:12.928 --> 16:14.103
-CONGRATULATIONS.

16:14.234 --> 16:15.409
-GAYLE: THANKS, STEPHANIE.

16:16.236 --> 16:18.978
WELL, IF AT FIRST
YOU DON'T SUCCEED...

16:19.108 --> 16:20.936
-[LAUGHS]

16:21.067 --> 16:22.720
-SO, WHERE'S THE
WEDDING GOING TO BE?

16:22.851 --> 16:24.984
-WELL, THE ONLY
PLACE WE COULD AFFORD.

16:25.941 --> 16:26.724
THE BEACH.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.378
-[LAUGHS]

16:36.386 --> 16:37.387
-STEPHANIE!

16:39.302 --> 16:40.216
STEPHANIE!

16:43.002 --> 16:43.959
STEPHANIE.

16:44.090 --> 16:45.569
-WHAT IS IT, C.J.?

16:45.700 --> 16:47.310
-I JUST WANTED TO MAKE
SURE THAT YOU'RE OKAY.

16:48.268 --> 16:49.443
-WHY WOULDN'T I BE OKAY?

16:50.139 --> 16:51.619
I MEAN, YOU KNOW PERFECTLY
WELL THAT MY RELATIONSHIP

16:51.749 --> 16:53.142
WITH MITCH IS STRICTLY PLATONIC.

16:53.273 --> 16:55.101
-I ALSO KNOW THAT
DEEP IN YOUR HEART,

16:55.231 --> 16:56.667
THERE'S ALWAYS BEEN THIS
LITTLE FLICKER OF HOPE

16:56.798 --> 16:58.278
THAT YOU AND MITCH MIGHT--

16:58.408 --> 16:59.801
-WELL, THAT FLICKER
WENT OUT A LONG TIME AGO.

17:01.542 --> 17:03.544
LOOK, I GOTTA GO.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

17:05.675 --> 17:07.722
-[SOFT MUSIC]

17:16.425 --> 17:19.125
-[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

17:34.531 --> 17:37.186
-OH, MAN! GEEZ.

17:37.317 --> 17:38.361
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

17:39.449 --> 17:40.624
YOU NEED A BREAK?

17:40.755 --> 17:42.931
-I THINK I HEARD
SOMETHING POP. OW.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.411
-YEAH, RIGHT.

17:45.020 --> 17:46.717
-AFRAID YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GO ON WITHOUT ME.

17:46.848 --> 17:48.589
THIS THUNDER ACHES
SOMETHING FIERCE.

17:49.198 --> 17:52.593
-CUT THE CRAP, LOGAN. THERE'S
NOTHING WRONG WITH YOU.

17:53.942 --> 17:56.466
YOU MIGHT BE ABLE TO FOOL
CAROLINE WITH THAT PHONY CHARM,

17:57.163 --> 17:58.033
BUT NOT ME.

17:59.078 --> 18:00.862
-ARE YOU CALLING
ME A LIAR, MATE?

18:01.645 --> 18:03.908
-YEAH. WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO ABOUT IT?

18:05.214 --> 18:08.696
-WELL, THERE'S NOT MUCH
I CAN DO IN MY CONDITION.

18:27.889 --> 18:29.586
-OKAY, GUYS. LET'S
BACK UP A LITTLE BIT.

18:29.717 --> 18:32.023
THAT TIDE IS VERY STRONG.

18:33.895 --> 18:35.940
DOES ANYBODY KNOW WHAT
CAUSES THE TIDE TO COME IN?

18:36.071 --> 18:38.073
-I DO. THE MOON.

18:38.204 --> 18:40.119
-VERY GOOD, ANNIE, YOU'RE RIGHT.

18:40.641 --> 18:42.773
THE GRAVITATIONAL PULL
OF THE SUN AND THE MOON

18:42.904 --> 18:45.907
CAUSES THE SURFACE LEVEL OF
THE OCEAN TO RISE AND FALL.

18:50.651 --> 18:52.957
NO, GUYS, COME ON!
GET OUT OF THE WATER!

18:54.742 --> 18:57.745
BOYS, LOOK OUT! OH, MY GOD!

18:57.875 --> 19:00.313
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:05.535 --> 19:07.146
SWIM TO THE ROCKS!

19:08.799 --> 19:10.671
-[KIDS YELLING]

19:12.890 --> 19:14.892
BOYS! SWIM!

19:24.772 --> 19:29.080
ANNIE! GO TO THE ROAD
TO GET HELP, NOW!

19:42.485 --> 19:43.791
-STOP!

19:44.835 --> 19:46.010
STOP!

19:50.014 --> 19:51.929
-WHAT'S WRONG?

19:52.060 --> 19:52.800
-THERE'S SOME KIDS
THAT FELL IN THE WATER
AND THEY CAN'T GET OUT.

19:52.930 --> 19:54.062
-WHERE ARE THEY?

20:06.596 --> 20:08.337
-[RADIO STATIC]

20:08.468 --> 20:10.383
-CODE THREE, VICTIMS
STRANDED ON THE ROCKS

20:10.513 --> 20:13.516
AT LEO CREILA, ALL AVAILABLE
UNITS RESPOND IMMEDIATELY.

20:13.647 --> 20:15.649
-WE'RE THE ONLY ONES WHO
CAN GET THERE FROM THE WATER.

20:15.779 --> 20:17.303
THE SCARAB CAN'T GET
THROUGH THE ROCKS.

20:17.433 --> 20:18.347
-HOW FAR IS IT?

20:18.478 --> 20:19.653
-JUST AROUND THE POINT.

20:19.783 --> 20:21.002
-COME ON, LET'S GO.

20:27.617 --> 20:29.053
-I THOUGHT YOU COULDN'T ROW.

20:29.184 --> 20:31.012
-I'LL LIVE WITH
THE PAIN, COME ON.

20:31.142 --> 20:32.753
NO MORE WANKERING OFF, LET'S GO.

20:33.710 --> 20:36.104
-[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

20:58.561 --> 21:00.607
-[KIDS YELLING]

21:13.576 --> 21:16.405
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

21:29.026 --> 21:31.420
-THERE THEY ARE.
FULL SPEED AHEAD.

21:37.948 --> 21:40.386
-HOLD ON. TAKE THE CAN.

21:43.084 --> 21:44.912
-JUST BE CAREFUL WHEN
WE GET TO THE ROCKS.

21:45.042 --> 21:46.740
WE DON'T WANT TO
HIT THE VICTIMS.

21:56.097 --> 21:57.316
-STEPHANIE: HELP
ME GET THEM ABOARD.

21:59.753 --> 22:02.321
-LOGAN, HERE.

22:03.800 --> 22:04.888
UP YOU GO.

22:06.063 --> 22:07.282
THAT A BOY.

22:09.502 --> 22:10.503
-LOGAN.

22:11.199 --> 22:12.983
-OKAY, LET ME HAVE
HIM, LIEUTENANT.

22:13.114 --> 22:14.463
-IT'S OKAY.

22:14.594 --> 22:15.203
-LOGAN: COME ON.
-IT'S OKAY.

22:47.191 --> 22:50.412
-YEAH! GONNA HIT
THE WATER, SEE YA!

22:52.458 --> 22:54.024
-GAYLE: LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON.

22:57.071 --> 23:00.901
YOU KNOW, MY BIGGEST
REGRET IS THAT I MISSED

23:01.031 --> 23:02.250
WATCHING HOBIE GROW UP.

23:03.599 --> 23:05.558
-COME ON, NOW. YOU
STILL GOT A WAYS TO GO.

23:05.688 --> 23:06.950
-YEAH.
-MITCH: THERE'S A CHANCE.

23:09.039 --> 23:11.302
-SO, HOW WOULD YOU FEEL
ABOUT HAVING ANOTHER ONE?

23:11.433 --> 23:13.174
-I LIKE TRYING.

23:13.304 --> 23:14.262
-[LAUGHS]

23:17.047 --> 23:19.136
-TRYING IS NEVER OUR PROBLEM.

23:20.311 --> 23:22.575
BUT YOU KNOW, THIS TIME'S
GOTTA BE DIFFERENT, MITCH.

23:23.750 --> 23:25.926
WE CAN'T AFFORD TO
REPEAT THE SAME MISTAKES.

23:27.318 --> 23:29.712
-YOU MEAN LIKE DESERTING
YOU ON OUR ANNIVERSARY

23:29.843 --> 23:30.670
TO MAKE A BODY SEARCH, RIGHT?

23:30.800 --> 23:32.193
THAT SORT OF THING?

23:32.323 --> 23:34.238
-YEAH, YOU KNOW, I
STILL HAVEN'T COMPLETELY

23:34.369 --> 23:36.023
FORGIVEN YOU FOR THAT.

23:36.153 --> 23:38.025
I MEAN, YOU LEFT ME AT THE
MOST EXPENSIVE RESTAURANT

23:38.155 --> 23:39.896
IN MALIBU WITHOUT A PURSE,

23:40.027 --> 23:42.725
AND I HAD TO BORROW MONEY FROM
THAT GUY TO PAY THE CHECK.

23:42.856 --> 23:46.163
-WAIT A SECOND, AS I RECALL,
I WAS NOT THE ONLY ONE

23:46.294 --> 23:47.904
WHO PUT CAREER ABOVE MARRIAGE.

23:48.035 --> 23:50.429
-I KNOW, I KNOW. I WAS
AS GUILTY AS YOU WERE.

23:51.995 --> 23:55.259
THAT'S WHY I'M SAYING THAT
THIS TIME I REALLY WANT US

23:55.390 --> 23:58.828
TO PUT OUR FAMILY FIRST, OKAY?

23:58.959 --> 24:00.961
-NO PROBLEM.

24:04.268 --> 24:05.618
[LAUGHS]

24:07.707 --> 24:09.535
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

24:11.101 --> 24:12.494
-I'M KISSING HER.

24:12.625 --> 24:13.930
-THE GROOM IS NOT
ALLOWED TO SEE THE BRIDE

24:14.061 --> 24:15.062
THE DAY OF THE WEDDING.

24:15.192 --> 24:17.238
IT'S BAD LUCK. GAYLE, GET IN.

24:17.368 --> 24:20.676
-MAYBE I BETTER TRY AND
MAKE MYSELF PRESENTABLE.

24:21.460 --> 24:22.461
-COME ON.

24:22.591 --> 24:23.766
-SEE YOU SOON.

24:25.246 --> 24:26.813
-BAD, BAD LUCK.

24:36.431 --> 24:37.432
-MAN: EASY WITH IT.

24:37.563 --> 24:38.825
-OKAY, I GOT IT. THERE WE GO.

24:40.000 --> 24:40.957
-NICE.

24:44.657 --> 24:46.441
-C.J.: CAREFUL, GUYS,
GO SLOW OR YOU'RE GONNA

24:46.572 --> 24:47.486
MUNCH THE CAKE.

24:58.192 --> 24:59.280
-ALLOW ME.

25:03.719 --> 25:05.112
YOU LOOK SMASHING.

25:05.242 --> 25:06.243
-THANK YOU.

25:06.374 --> 25:07.506
-OH, YOU, TOO, LIEUTENANT.

25:08.594 --> 25:09.595
SHALL WE?

25:13.642 --> 25:15.818
-NO OFFENSE, BUT YOUR SISTER'S
GOT LOUSY TASTE IN MEN.

25:15.949 --> 25:17.516
-MATT.

25:17.646 --> 25:19.082
-I DON'T CARE WHAT
YOU SAW AT LEO CREILA.

25:19.213 --> 25:20.997
I STILL SAY HE'S NOT
FIT TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

25:21.128 --> 25:22.346
-OH, YEAH? WHY NOT?

25:22.912 --> 25:25.915
-BECAUSE HE'S LAZY,
RECKLESS, IRRESPONSIBLE.

25:26.046 --> 25:28.004
YOU CAN'T BELIEVE
A WORD HE SAYS.

25:28.135 --> 25:29.919
PLUS, I DON'T LIKE WORKING
WITH A GUY WHO'S ONLY

25:30.050 --> 25:31.442
OUT FOR HIMSELF.

25:31.573 --> 25:32.748
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THE LAST PART.

25:34.794 --> 25:36.709
HE'S RECOMMENDED YOU
FOR THE MEDAL OF VALOR.

25:37.623 --> 25:38.493
-WHAT?

25:42.453 --> 25:43.498
-YOU WANNA--

25:44.978 --> 25:45.935
[HUFFS]

25:47.546 --> 25:50.157
I DON'T REMEMBER BEING
THIS NERVOUS THE LAST TIME.

25:50.287 --> 25:51.680
-GARNER: YOU HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS?

25:51.811 --> 25:53.943
-NO, NO, I'M NOT. IT'S
JUST THAT YOU KNOW,

25:54.509 --> 25:56.990
THERE'S A LOT MORE AT STAKE
THE SECOND TIME AROUND.
THERES...

25:58.078 --> 25:59.601
A BIT MORE PRESSURE
TO GET IT RIGHT.

25:59.732 --> 26:01.342
-WELL, IF ANYBODY CAN
HANDLE THE PRESSURE,

26:01.472 --> 26:02.430
MY FRIEND, IT'S YOU.

26:04.084 --> 26:06.521
AH, LOOK, C.J. ASKED ME
TO DOUBLE AS AN USHER,

26:06.652 --> 26:08.349
SO YOU BETTER GIVE
ME THAT RING NOW.

26:08.958 --> 26:09.742
-THE RING.

26:09.872 --> 26:10.873
-THE RING.

26:11.004 --> 26:12.309
-OH! THE RING, THE RING.

26:12.440 --> 26:14.137
[LAUGHS] THE RING.

26:15.530 --> 26:16.618
THE RING.

26:18.707 --> 26:20.535
YOU KNOW THIS IS THE
SAME RING I GAVE GAYLE

26:20.666 --> 26:22.189
ON OUR FIRST WEDDING DAY.

26:22.319 --> 26:23.625
-I THOUGHT SHE GAVE IT
BACK TO YOU WHEN YOU SPLIT.

26:23.756 --> 26:24.887
-NO, ACTUALLY,
SHE THREW IT AT ME.

26:25.627 --> 26:26.889
HIT ME RIGHT IN
BETWEEN THE EYES.

26:27.020 --> 26:28.761
-[LAUGHS] OUCH.

26:31.154 --> 26:32.895
-I NEVER BRING MYSELF
TO GET RID OF IT.

26:33.504 --> 26:36.682
-THAT IS BECAUSE YOU ARE
A SENTIMENTAL FOOL, BUDDY.

26:36.812 --> 26:37.639
-YEAH.

26:37.770 --> 26:40.120
-BUT THIS TIME, IT PAID OFF.

26:41.425 --> 26:42.296
GOOD LUCK, MY FRIEND.

26:43.906 --> 26:44.733
-THANKS.

26:45.778 --> 26:46.605
-SEE YOU AT THE ALTER.

26:46.735 --> 26:49.782
-YEAH. [SIGHS HEAVILY]

26:59.530 --> 27:00.619
-HEY, YOU LOOK GREAT.

27:00.749 --> 27:03.186
-HEY. [LAUGHS] THANKS.

27:04.492 --> 27:05.798
SO, DO YOU.

27:05.928 --> 27:07.364
-I JUST CAME BY TO
PICK UP MY BEEPER

27:08.539 --> 27:09.889
AND TO WISH YOU GOOD LUCK.

27:10.977 --> 27:11.978
-THANK YOU.

27:13.544 --> 27:15.677
-YOUR TIE IS CROOKED.

27:15.808 --> 27:16.591
-UM...

27:16.722 --> 27:17.679
-I'LL FIX IT.

27:17.810 --> 27:20.682
-OKAY. I'M A MESS.

27:22.858 --> 27:24.381
-LOOK, I HOPE YOU DON'T
TAKE THIS THE WRONG WAY

27:24.512 --> 27:26.688
OR ANYTHING, I MEAN,
WE'VE BEEN FRIENDS

27:26.819 --> 27:28.908
FOR A LONG TIME AND YOU
KNOW THAT I ONLY WANT

27:29.038 --> 27:30.257
WHAT'S BEST FOR YOU, BUT...

27:33.260 --> 27:35.392
THIS IS HAPPENING
SO FAST, YOU KNOW?

27:35.523 --> 27:37.046
YOU'RE NOT USUALLY
THIS IMPULSIVE.

27:37.177 --> 27:39.440
ARE YOU SURE YOU'VE REALLY
THOUGHT THIS THING OUT?

27:41.529 --> 27:42.922
I KNOW, I'M SORRY.

27:43.052 --> 27:45.098
-NO, NO, IT'S A PERFECTLY
LEGITIMATE QUESTION.

27:45.228 --> 27:46.926
-NO, IT ISN'T. I SHOULD
JUST KEEP MY BIG MOUTH SHUT--

27:47.056 --> 27:49.929
-THE TRUTH IS I HAVEN'T
COMPLETELY THOUGHT IT OUT.

27:51.365 --> 27:53.323
IT'S JUST THAT SOMETIMES
YOU JUST GOTTA GO

27:53.454 --> 27:54.324
ON YOUR INSTINCTS.

27:56.022 --> 27:57.980
-YOU ALWAYS HAD GOOD INSTINCTS.

28:00.896 --> 28:02.158
-THANKS FOR LOOKING OUT FOR ME.

28:06.293 --> 28:07.511
COME HERE.

28:09.992 --> 28:14.475
-[CALMING MUSIC]

28:26.226 --> 28:29.838
♪ ALL THE WARMTH OF THE SUN

28:29.969 --> 28:32.711
♪ IS IN YOU

28:34.495 --> 28:40.327
