♪ YOU'RE EVERYTHING

31:19.094 --> 31:19.965
-WOMAN: IS THAT BETTER?

31:20.095 --> 31:21.314
-MAN: THAT'S GREAT.

31:22.489 --> 31:23.969
-[LAUGHS]

31:27.276 --> 31:28.712
-HAVE YOU GOT SOMETHING?

31:35.676 --> 31:39.201
-DANNY! WE GOT MORE
THAN BAIT IN THE SACK!

31:39.332 --> 31:40.899
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO USE THE WRETCH!

31:55.087 --> 31:56.349
-WOMAN: WHAT IS IT?

31:56.479 --> 31:57.437
-I DON'T KNOW.

31:59.656 --> 32:02.137
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:02.268 --> 32:05.358
-OH, MY GOD. IT'S AN OLD MINE!

32:10.232 --> 32:11.581
IT'S COMING AT THE BOAT!

32:13.670 --> 32:14.976
CUT IT LOOSE!

32:17.370 --> 32:19.024
-IT'S NOT STOPPING!

32:23.245 --> 32:25.247
-[SHOUTING OVER ONE ANOTHER]

32:32.472 --> 32:34.517
-AND SO AS YOU PLEDGE
YOUR LOVE TO EACH OTHER

32:34.648 --> 32:37.303
AND TO YOUR FAMILY
AND FRIENDS, REMEMBER,

32:37.433 --> 32:39.653
LIKE THE WAVES THAT
WASH AWAY THE FOOTPRINTS

32:39.783 --> 32:42.961
IN THE SAND, THE
WORDS YOU SPEAK TODAY,

32:43.091 --> 32:45.876
MAY SOON BE FORGOTTEN,
BUT THE COMMITMENT

32:46.007 --> 32:48.053
THAT YOU MAKE IN YOUR
HEART IS ETERNAL.

32:49.750 --> 32:54.059
MITCH AND GAYLE, YOU'RE LIVING
PROOF OF THE EVERLASTING

32:54.189 --> 32:57.366
POWER OF LOVE AND IT'S
A PRIVILEGE TO BE A PART

32:57.497 --> 32:58.585
OF YOUR REUNION.

32:59.368 --> 33:02.502
NOW HAVING SAID THAT, LET'S
GET ON WITH THE GOOD STUFF.

33:02.632 --> 33:04.199
-YES.

33:04.330 --> 33:06.419
-IF THE BEST MAN
WILL PRESENT THE RING.

33:17.821 --> 33:21.912
-YOU KEPT IT ALL
THESE YEARS. GOD.

33:23.305 --> 33:24.741
-I HOPE IT STILL FITS.

33:26.439 --> 33:31.009
-PLACE THE RING UPON HER
FINGER AND REPEAT AFTER ME.

33:34.447 --> 33:37.450
I, MITCHELL BUCHANNON.

33:38.668 --> 33:41.062
-I, MITCHELL BUCHANNON.

33:41.193 --> 33:42.759
TAKE--
-[BEEPING]

33:42.890 --> 33:45.893
-[MURMURING OVER ONE ANOTHER]

33:47.677 --> 33:49.418
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

33:51.072 --> 33:52.073
-AH...

33:54.075 --> 33:56.469
THAT'S HEADQUARTERS.
SOMETHING'S UP.

33:56.599 --> 34:00.603
-MITCH, LET THEM TAKE CARE
OF IT. YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED.

34:00.734 --> 34:02.823
-MITCH, WE GOTTA CALL IT IN.

34:05.217 --> 34:07.436
-LOOK, THE PHONE'S RIGHT
HERE. IT'LL JUST TAKE A SECOND.

34:07.567 --> 34:08.393
JUST A SECOND.

34:12.311 --> 34:14.574
-MITCH: JOHN, IT'S
MITCH. WHAT'S GOING ON?

34:14.704 --> 34:17.228
WAIT A MINUTE, SLOW DOWN.
YEAH, OKAY, I GOT IT.

34:17.359 --> 34:19.274
TELL HIM WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

34:22.016 --> 34:23.931
FISHING BOAT'S GOING
DOWN OVER PALACE VERDIS.

34:24.062 --> 34:26.411
45 PEOPLE ON BOARD. LET'S GO!

34:27.282 --> 34:28.717
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]
-MITCH.

34:28.849 --> 34:31.808
-GAYLE, I'M SORRY, BUT
I CAN'T DO THIS NOW.

34:32.940 --> 34:34.114
-CAN YOU STICK
AROUND FOR AWHILE?

34:34.246 --> 34:35.943
-UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES, YES.

34:36.074 --> 34:40.469
-I'LL BE BACK AS SOON
AS I CAN. I LOVE YOU!

34:47.781 --> 34:51.828
-[SIRENS BLARING]

35:04.711 --> 35:07.801
-[SCREAMS]

35:20.988 --> 35:23.208
-HELP ME! HE CAN'T SWIM!

35:23.338 --> 35:24.513
HE'S DISABLED!

35:26.515 --> 35:28.038
-THIS IS BUCHANNON
ON SCARAB ONE.

35:28.169 --> 35:29.649
WE'RE LOOKING AT A LOT
OF SMOKE AND FLAME.

35:29.779 --> 35:31.520
MAKE SURE WE GET A FIRE
BOAT OUT HERE RIGHT AWAY.

35:36.438 --> 35:39.180
-JIMMY! THE CABIN HOUSE
IS ON FIRE!

35:39.311 --> 35:40.921
-MAN: EVERYBODY,
GET OFF THE BOAT!

35:41.051 --> 35:42.662
-MAN: COME ON! GET OFF!

35:42.792 --> 35:45.360
-HELP! HELP!

35:54.369 --> 35:56.589
-GET EVERYBODY OFF, NOW!

36:03.857 --> 36:05.902
GO! IT'S GONNA BLOW!

36:06.033 --> 36:07.861
-[SCREAMS]

36:16.870 --> 36:18.263
-THERE!

36:23.746 --> 36:25.400
-HELP!

36:32.277 --> 36:33.278
HELP!

36:42.852 --> 36:44.941
HELP ME, HELP MY HUSBAND!

36:45.072 --> 36:47.988
HE CAN'T SWIM! SOMEBODY
HELP MY HUSBAND!

36:49.642 --> 36:50.947
-I GOT YOU!
-WOMAN: SOMEBODY HELP!

36:53.776 --> 36:55.300
-YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.
WE'LL GET YOUR HUSBAND.

36:55.430 --> 36:57.215
SOMEONE WILL GET YOUR
HUSBAND. YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

36:57.345 --> 36:58.694
-WOMAN: HE CAN'T SWIM!

36:59.521 --> 37:00.522
-HELP! HELP!

37:00.653 --> 37:02.176
-HERE! TAKE MY HAND.

37:13.361 --> 37:15.407
-WOMAN: HELP, HELP! HENRY!

37:15.537 --> 37:16.973
-YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

37:21.239 --> 37:23.632
-OKAY, OKAY. TAKE THIS.

37:24.894 --> 37:26.113
-LOGAN: GRAB MY HAND.

37:27.375 --> 37:28.246
OKAY.

37:30.335 --> 37:32.859
-[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

37:37.037 --> 37:39.082
-KEEP GOING. GO, GO.

37:39.213 --> 37:40.301
NICE WORK.

37:42.608 --> 37:45.524
COME ON, LET'S GO. I GOT
A WEDDING TO GET BACK TO.

37:53.445 --> 37:54.576
WHERE'S GAYLE?

37:54.707 --> 37:58.232
-SHE TOOK A WALK
DOWN THE BEACH.

38:03.150 --> 38:04.282
-THANKS.

38:19.471 --> 38:20.298
GAYLE?

38:21.821 --> 38:23.213
COME ON, LET'S GO BACK.

38:24.171 --> 38:25.346
-I CAN'T.

38:26.478 --> 38:28.001
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN YOU CAN'T?

38:29.132 --> 38:33.441
-TALK ABOUT DEJA VU. THAT
WAS JUST LIKE OUR ANNIVERSARY.

38:34.660 --> 38:35.791
-WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO?

38:35.922 --> 38:37.532
-EXACTLY WHAT YOU DID DO.

38:39.229 --> 38:40.666
MITCH, THAT'S WHO YOU ARE.

38:40.796 --> 38:44.539
I HAD FORGOTTEN THAT
YOU NEVER GO OFF DUTY.

38:45.105 --> 38:47.150
YOU'RE A LIFEGUARD
24 HOURS A DAY

38:47.281 --> 38:49.718
AND THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO ABOUT IT.

38:49.849 --> 38:50.937
-YEAH, THERE IS.

38:52.591 --> 38:53.983
YOU COULD ACCEPT IT.

38:58.640 --> 38:59.859
I THOUGHT YOU HAD.

39:00.773 --> 39:03.036
-YEAH, WELL, I
THOUGHT I HAD TOO.

39:03.993 --> 39:05.343
-I LOVE YOU.

39:06.344 --> 39:07.562
-I LOVE YOU.

39:09.869 --> 39:14.308
I JUST THINK THAT WE'RE-- WE GOT
A LITTLE AHEAD OF OURSELVES.

39:21.576 --> 39:25.450
-GAYLE, WE WALK
AWAY FROM THIS NOW,

39:27.495 --> 39:30.498
WE COULD REGRET THIS FOR
THE REST OF OUR LIVES.

39:36.548 --> 39:38.027
-I'M SORRY, MITCH.

39:53.129 --> 39:54.392
-[LAUGHS]

40:10.277 --> 40:11.713
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

40:11.844 --> 40:12.932
-JUST LEAVE ME ALONE.

40:13.062 --> 40:15.325
-I KNOW, I KNOW,
PAL. I'M SORRY.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.154
YOU JUST KEEP GETTING
CAUGHT IN THE MIDDLE.

40:19.417 --> 40:20.983
-I SHOULD'VE NEVER
GOT MY HOPES UP.

40:21.114 --> 40:22.855
I KNEW IT WAS TOO
GOOD TO BE TRUE.

40:24.509 --> 40:26.467
-DID YOUR MOM TALK TO
YOU BEFORE SHE LEFT?

40:27.163 --> 40:28.208
-YEAH.

40:28.774 --> 40:31.124
-DID SHE TELL YOU WHY
SHE CHANGED HER MIND?

40:32.952 --> 40:34.867
IT DOESN'T MEAN SHE
DOESN'T LOVE YOU ANY LESS.

40:36.825 --> 40:38.000
-I JUST DON'T GET IT.

40:38.784 --> 40:41.874
HOW CAN YOU COME SO CLOSE
AND THEN HAVE IT ALL

40:42.004 --> 40:42.875
BLOW UP IN YOUR FACE?

40:45.965 --> 40:47.009
-I DON'T KNOW, PAL.

40:48.489 --> 40:49.621
IF I HAD THE ANSWER TO THAT ONE,

40:49.751 --> 40:50.970
SAVE US ALL A LOT OF PAIN.

40:52.580 --> 40:53.625
I KNOW ONE THING.

40:55.627 --> 40:56.628
WHEN YOUR DREAMS ARE SHATTERED,

40:56.758 --> 40:58.238
THERE'S ONLY ONE THING TO DO.

40:58.368 --> 41:00.893
PICK UP THE PIECES AND
START BUILDING A NEW ONE.

41:04.287 --> 41:05.114
LET'S GO HOME.

41:05.245 --> 41:06.420
-ALL RIGHT.

41:12.600 --> 41:15.603
WHOA. DID YOU FEEL THAT?

41:17.083 --> 41:18.388
MY FIRST AFTERSHOCK.

41:19.694 --> 41:20.695
-WELCOME HOME?

41:20.826 --> 41:22.480
-YEAH.

41:25.439 --> 41:30.488
-[SOOTHING MUSIC]

41:36.102 --> 41:37.886
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
